{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantProtocol"]]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/variantprotocol\/getdata()"]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"getData","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"text":"gconstpointer","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gconstpointer","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"?","kind":"text"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"level":2,"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"code":"value","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is a fixed-sized value that was deserialized from a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"corrupted serialized container then "},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" may be returned.  In this","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"case, the proper thing to do is typically to use the appropriate"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"number of nul bytes in place of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"value"},{"text":".  If ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"value"},{"type":"text","text":" is not fixed-sized"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"then ","type":"text"},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is never returned."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In the case that "},{"code":"value","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is already in serialized form, this function"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"O(1)"},{"text":".  If the value is not already in serialized form,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"serialization occurs implicitly and is approximately "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"O(n)"},{"text":" in the size","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of the result."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To deserialize the data returned by this function, in addition to the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"serialized data, you must know the type of the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant"},{"type":"text","text":", and (if the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"machine might be different) the endianness of the machine that stored","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"it. As a result, file formats or network messages that incorporate"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"serialized "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GVariants"},{"type":"text","text":" must include this information either"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"implicitly (for instance “the file always contains a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"G_VARIANT_TYPE_VARIANT","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and it is always in little-endian order”) or"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"explicitly (by storing the type and\/or endianness in addition to the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"serialized data).","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantProtocol\/getData()","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"metadata":{"extendedModule":"GLib","symbolKind":"method","role":"symbol","title":"getData()","roleHeading":"Instance Method","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"getData","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"gconstpointer","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gconstpointer"},{"text":"?","kind":"text"}],"externalID":"s:4GLib15VariantProtocolPAAE7getDataSVSgyF"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Returns a pointer to the serialized form of a "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"The returned data may not be in fully-normalised form if read from an"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"untrusted source.  The returned data must not be freed; it remains","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"valid for as long as ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"value"},{"text":" exists.","type":"text"}],"sections":[],"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/VariantProtocol/getData()":{"title":"getData()","role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"getData"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"gconstpointer","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gconstpointer"},{"text":"?","kind":"text"}],"type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Returns a pointer to the serialized form of a "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The returned data may not be in fully-normalised form if read from an","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"untrusted source.  The returned data must not be freed; it remains"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"valid for as long as ","type":"text"},{"code":"value","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" exists."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantProtocol\/getData()","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/variantprotocol\/getdata()"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/VariantProtocol":{"title":"VariantProtocol","abstract":[{"code":"GVariant","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is a variant datatype; it can contain one or more values","type":"text"},{"typ